"<b>Uncountable</b>, un-kown′ta-bl, <i>adj.</i> innumerable.—<i>adj.</i> <b>Uncount′ed</b>, not counted or numbered.",
"<b>Uncouple</b>, un-kup′l, <i>v.t.</i> to loose from being coupled: to disjoin: to set loose.—<i>adj.</i> <b>Uncoup′led</b>, not coupled: not married: (<i>her.</i>) <i>découplé</i>.",
"<b>Uncourteous</b>, un-kurt′yus, <i>adj.</i> not courteous.—<i>adv.</i> <b>Uncourt′eously</b>.",
