"<b>Underagent</b>, un-dėr-ā′jent, <i>n.</i> a subordinate agent.",
"<b>Underaid</b>, un-dėr-ād′, <i>v.t.</i> to aid secretly.",
"<b>Underbear</b>, un-dėr-bār′, <i>v.t.</i> (<i>Shak.</i>) to support, to endure, to line.—<i>n.</i> <b>Un′derbearer</b>.",
