"<b>Under-board</b>, un′dėr-bōrd, <i>adv.</i> (<i>obs.</i>) secretly—opp. to <i>Above-board</i>.",
"<b>Underbrace</b>, un-dėr-brās′, <i>v.t.</i> to fasten or fix underneath.",
"<b>Underbranch</b>, un′dėr-bransh, <i>n.</i> a small branch.",
"<b>Underbred</b>, un′dėr-bred, <i>adj.</i> of inferior breeding or manners, vulgar: not pure-bred.",
