"<td>",
"The Greek prefixes (<i>deca</i>, <i>hecto</i>, <i>kilo</i>, <i>myria</i>) denote multiplication.",
"The Latin prefixes (<i>deci</i>, <i>centi</i>, <i>milli</i>) denote division.",
"</td>",
"</tr>",
"<tr>",
"<td>SQUARE MEASURE.</td>",
"</tr>",
"<tr>",
"<td>The <b>ARE</b>, the unit of surface measure, is a square the side of which is ten mètres long.</td>",
"</tr>",
"<tr>",
"<td>",
"<table>",
"<tr>",
"<td>1 Are</td> <td>=</td> <td>100</td> <td>Square mètres.</td>",
"</tr>",
"<tr>",
"<td>1 Decare</td> <td>=</td> <td>10</td> <td>ares.</td>",
"</tr>",
"<tr>",
"<td>1 Hectare</td> <td>=</td> <td>100</td> <td>  \"</td>",
"</tr>",
"</table>",
"</td>",
"<td>",
"<table>",
"<tr>",
"<td>1 Déciare</td> <td>=</td> <td>1⁄10th</td> <td>of an are.</td>",
